			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Issuu (www.issuu.com) is revolutionizing the way people publish and distribute their publications. We&rsquo;re the fastest growing digital publishing platform with more than 4 million publications and over 50 million monthly readers. Founded in 2006 in Copenhagen, Denmark, Issuu has recently opened an office in Palo Alto, CA and we&rsquo;re looking for an intern to help us drive our growth in the US. This internship will be based in Palo Alto.</p>
<p>
The social media intern at Issuu will assist the head of marketing with various activities including social media planning, copywriting, posting across the social networks, moderating and engagement.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop programs to help us increase our social footprint</li>
<li>
Implement social analytics and &ldquo;listening&rdquo; tools and provide weekly reports</li>
<li>
Build our social media calendar</li>
<li>
Curate relevant and compelling content from Issuu</li>
<li>
Write on-brand copy for social and other marketing activities</li>
<li>
Investigate and recommend new/emerging social networks</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Demonstrated copywriting experience</li>
<li>
Demonstrated expertise in social media</li>
<li>
Working knowledge of Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest and other social platforms</li>
<li>
Striving to build a career in marketing</li>
<li>
BA/BS in marketing (recent grad) or rising senior</li>
<li>
Cross-cultural sensitivity</li>
<li>
Agility and able to work in &ldquo;real-time&rdquo; as required</li>
</ul>
<p>
Job details:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Job is located at our office in Palo Alto, CA.</li>
<li>
3 month full-time contract from June - August. 40 hours per week throughout the summer.</li>
<li>
Pay is hourly, competitive and commensurate with level of experience.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Ready to apply? Please submit the following:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Cover letter/note showcasing your writing skills and general personality and style</li>
<li>
Resume showcasing your relevant experience</li>
<li>
Links to social media destinations that show your work</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
