<strong>About this job</strong><br />
As a Business Analyst&nbsp; at Issuu, you will be part of a small, global team responsible for analyzing, and understanding the data behind our users actions.&nbsp; You&rsquo;re someone who can see stories through data spikes, and passionate about finding patterns through cohort analysis.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re looking for candidates who love to work cross-functionally across our product, engineering, marketing, and sales teams to help put together a holistic picture of what makes our users happy.&nbsp; If this sounds like you, read on to learn more details, or skip to the bottom and apply!&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Understand the data generated by Issuu&#39;s core infrastructure and client applications</li>
<li>
Work with all teams to understand their analytics goals, and evolve our systems to meet their needs on a timely basis</li>
<li>
Design, develop, test, launch new reports and dashboards into production.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BS or higher in Mathematics, Engineering or Computer Scrience</li>
<li>
2+ years experience in the reporting and data visualization space.</li>
<li>
Expert level skills in building custom reports and dashboards.</li>
<li>
Expert level skills in Schema design and Dimensional data modeling.</li>
<li>
Expert level ability to analyze data to identify deliverables, gaps and inconsistencies.</li>
<li>
Experience with software engineering best practices (e.g. unit testing, code reviews, design documentation)</li>
<li>
Experience working with data using various programming languages, e.g. Python, Perl to extract raw data and render it into custom reports/dashboards</li>
<li>
Experience building custom reports using multiple tools like Tableau.</li>
<li>
Ability to write efficient SQL statements.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Benefits</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Competitive compensation package</li>
<li>
A sleek mac and a pretty sweet desk setup</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ll be a part of Issuu, an amazing place with room for parents, vegetarians, geeks, weirdos and the occasional normal guy</li>
<li>
Walking distance to the Cal-train and monthly passes for public transportation, or parking</li>
<li>
Catered lunches, team events, and a huge opportunity to do something big<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Details</strong><br />
Our office is in downtown Palo Alto, CA.<br />
Full time role, with a 3 month probationary period<br />
Pay is salary, competitive and commensurate with level of experience.</p>
